<h1>Graphviz</h1>

<div class='t'>
Graphviz stands for <i>graph visualization software</i>. Graphs are created by describing them in a specifically created language: <a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/tools/Graphviz/dot/index'>dot</a>. </div>

<div class='t'>
Some examples can be found <a href='examples/index'>here</a>. </div>
<div class='h'>
<h2 id='graphviz-installation'>Installing Graphviz</h2>
<div class='t'>
  On <a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/Windows/index'>Windows</a>, Graphviz can be installed with <a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/Windows/Chocolatey/index'>Chocolatey</a> </div><pre class='code'><a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/Windows/dirs/ProgramData/chocolatey/bin/choco_exe'>choco</a> install -y graphviz
</pre>
</div>
<div class='h'>
<h2>Some important attributes</h2>
<div class='t'>
  Some (imho) important <a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/tools/Graphviz/attributes/index'>attributes</a> and <a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/tools/Graphviz/attributes/types/index'>attribute types</a> are <ul>
<li>    <a href='https://renenyffenegger.ch/notes/tools/Graphviz/attributes/style'><code>style</code></a> 
<li>    <a href='attributes/label/index'><code>label</code></a> 
<li>    <a href='attributes/shape/index'><code>shape</code></a> (for <a href='elems/node/index'>nodes</a>) 
<li>    <a href='attributes/_color/index'>Color related attributes</a> </ul></div>
</div>
<div class='h'>
<h2>Four phases when drawing</h2>
<div class='t'>
  A graph is created in four phases: <ul>
<li>    Break cycles so that the graph becomes acyclic 
<li>    Assign a <i>rank</i> for each <i>node</i> (usually y-coordinate). 
<li>    Order nodes on same rank to avoid crossing (of edges?) 
<li>    Create splines between nodes </ul></div>
</div>
<div class='h'>
<h2>Useful command line options</h2>
<div class='t'>
  Setting dpi (or resulution) of generated graphs: <code>-Gdpi=300</code>. </div>
</div>
<div class='h'>
<h2>Strings vs HTML strings</h2>
<div class='t'>
  Ordinary strings are delimited with apostrophes: <code>"…"</code> </div>
<div class='g'></div>
<div class='t'>
  HTML strings are delimited by angle bracktes: <code>&lt;…&gt;</code> </div>
</div>
